{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9371455-3bca-4b6b-a076-30290ac27e19","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (replaces both the framework and test adapter)\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <!-- Remove this -->\n  <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n\n<!-- Replace with -->\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**In your test code** — no changes needed. The `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace, `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and `Assert` APIs are all preserved in MSTest v3.\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1aa7bb70-2ddf-47fc-9065-b961c04c5153","outputTokens":290,"requestId":"B819:310A41:E2A96F:F03F82:6A044D57"},"id":"32d2303b-ade4-4aba-8816-3ef6209c5a8f","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:27.157Z","parentId":"4a58e326-e940-4936-a29c-dcb439753023"}
